creditline: Lent by John and Carol Jean Carlisle
description: Fine line 5-pointed star with stylized plants, rim deged with inverted triangles, 'This basket was bought by Henry L. George in the year 1890 from Geronimo's daughter and it was made by her mother, the wife of Geronimo; at that time Geronimo was still on the war path.  He was captured shortly after near the Mexican line in the mountains' - on back of an old R.L. Balke blanket tag.-Apache Coiled Basket
title: Apache coiled basket
